Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text: - Garcia is very off. There are moments where he's playing well, but this is mostly an off night. Look to other dates for good music.
more to the dead even if jerry  having a off night there some real gems give it a ear

This is the best (SBD) course. Pitch is correct, etc.  Everybody agrees: Jerry is more "miss" than "hit". 

Bobby's setbreak announcement is comical: He sounds amused by all the clams they've made throughout the 1st set. 

The magic happens for a few minutes during the drums -> "Eyes" transition (notice there was no 'space') ... Jerry noodles, the drummers stick around, and things light up momentarily. But then when Jerry sings that first line of the song, he sounds like he's cracking up. Either his voice is cracking, or he's losing his shit laughing. I suspect the latter. 

This was probably a fun show to attend.
